<p><ent>Stogy</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Stogy
<hw>Sto"gy</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Stogies</plw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr></plu>. <altsp>[Written also <asp>stogie</asp>.]</altsp>
<ety>[<ets>Colloq</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A stout, coarse boot or
shoe; a brogan.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A kind of cheap, but not necessary inferior, cigar
made in the form of a cylindrical roll.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stoic</ent>⟦br⟧
